The paper focuses on privacy-preserving techniques for solving combinatorial optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The problem being addressed is the distributed graph coloring problem, which involves distributed computing and communication (cs.DC) as well as graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of approximation algorithms and heuristics, which are topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT), respectively.
